You can use different style sheets for this wiki.  The default is rather plain, we know.
If you would like to add more colors or use fancy fonts, pick another style sheet and
use it.  We're also interested in finding more style sheets, so there are links to CSS
sources as well for you to study and adapt -- and share.  :)

== Style Sheets ==

You can change the theme used for this wiki using one of the following links:

* [http://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/wiki.css Default CSS] with default theme ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;theme=default;css= use it])

** Same CSS with more whitespace around headers and small-caps theme ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;theme=typo;css= use it])

** Same CSS with big fonts theme: 14/16 Lucida Bright ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;theme=big;css= use it])

** Same CSS with medium fonts theme: 12/14 Lucida Bright ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;theme=medium;css= use it])

** Same CSS with small fonts theme: 10/11 and your default font ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;theme=small;css= use it])

** Same CSS with tiny fonts theme: 8/9 and your default font
([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;theme=tiny;css= use it])

* [http://www.emacswiki.org/css/basic.css Basic CSS] for people that have tweaked their user CSS and only want the most basic style sheet ([EmacsWiki:action=browse;id=CSS;css=/css/basic.css use it])

